    {
      "id": "d8efbc3c_a4f43616",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/sdnc/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 39,
      "line": 62,
      "message": "This may be a misunderstanding on my part but as far as I was aware we needed this in sdnc/values.yaml if we wanted to use global values in onap/values.yaml. The onap ones would overwrite these but these would act as a default if someone deleted a value in onap/values. I deleted the cert-inits variables from this file because they weren't needed. Am I incorrect in this?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4893,
        "name": "Gerard Nugent",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "gerard.nugent@est.tech",
        "username": "egernug"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-29 18:09:55.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "d1780b00_83b8e56b",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "1a67ec4f_4735f09b",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/sdnc/templates/statefulset.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 40,
      "line": 29,
      "message": "Please add here the spec.selector part, which is visible in the \"original\" file.\nK8S spec apps/v1 won`t work without this property.\nWe`d need this complete section after the \"spec:\" :\n\n  selector:\n    matchLabels:\n      app: {{ include \"common.name\" . }}\n\nSee more here:\nhttps://kubernetes.io/blog/2019/07/18/api-deprecations-in-1-16/",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5597,
        "name": "Damian Nowak",
        "display_name": "Damian Nowak",
        "email": "damian.nowak@nokia.com",
        "username": "deen1985"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-30 08:02:33.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "8a27f257_2e90ba7a",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/sdnc/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 40,
      "line": 43,
      "message": "Check, if this is really the cert-service images, which You shall use here.\nhttps://docs.onap.org/projects/onap-aaf-certservice/en/latest/sections/release-notes.html# \n\nSee known issues section (for certservice client 1.0.0 image):\nKnown Issues\n\n        AAF-1132 - CertService Client returns exit status 5 when TLS configuration fails\n        PKCS12 certificates have jks extension",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5597,
        "name": "Damian Nowak",
        "display_name": "Damian Nowak",
        "email": "damian.nowak@nokia.com",
        "username": "deen1985"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-30 08:02:33.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "0e30006a_b1fa61fd",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/sdnc/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 40,
      "line": 46,
      "message": "Would it be posisble to consider here a more general folder name/structure?\ne.g. /etc/onap/certs/external ?\n\nWe`re in a process of migrating AAF-CertService, to be simply cert-service (not aaf anymore).\nAvoiding to use \"aaf\" will make this future proof.\n\n(Other projects use simply /etc/onap/certs - as they are using internal ONAP certs, since teh communicate with internal ONAP components only. Here I assume, we`d have internal certs towards internal ONAP components, and external certs towards Nfs external from ONAP.)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5597,
        "name": "Damian Nowak",
        "display_name": "Damian Nowak",
        "email": "damian.nowak@nokia.com",
        "username": "deen1985"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-30 08:02:33.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
